    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nFeature request: expose an option to configure LSP client logs. Sometimes it's spammy, but disabling logs obviously defeats its purpose. For logs I don't necessarily need all the time and only reference on occasion, I like to configure it to tmpfs, e.g. /tmp/nvim. That's where I keep my undo, swap, lsp server logs, etc.\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAn option to configure the location for LSP client logs.",
