            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Hmm, shada file also use `$XDG_STATE_HOME` so should be hardcoded to use the original `$XDG_STATE_HOME` if `$XDG_STATE_HOME` is to be redefined to tmpfs for the logs. I feel like it would make sense for a way to decouple the two since the shada file affects functionality but logs don't. \n\nI can understand why they might be tied together so I should probably just look to disable logging where possible as an alternative.",
